      <section eId="sec_25_15_97">
        <num>25-15-97</num>
        <content>
          <p>The owner or operator of a carnival ride may deny entry to a person to a carnival ride if in the owner's or operator's opinion the entry may jeopardize the safety of such person or the safety of any other person. Nothing in this Code section shall permit an owner or operator to deny an inspector access to a carnival ride when such inspector is acting within the scope of his or her duties under this article.</p>
